Truly a basic Mediterranean food hall for the mass. But seriously a $16 for a dish of lamb and rice. :(  I was excited to come here for a quick bite because it was cold and windy outside. This place seems to be perfect for a casual bite. The interior is very bare minimum with chair and table as well as a self service garbage can. I felt like coming to a high school cafeteria.  I was hoping for a ox tail however they are out. Their price list is super super confusing and I will suggest you just get what your heart wants and expect to pay a little extra. Disappointed with no ox tail, I settle with lamb and rice but didn't realize it was $16. Oh well this is prime real estate. Don't get me wrong thou. The lamb is delicious and I will say garment if packaged better.  Service is none. You will wait at the counter and pick your food. Clean up after yourself and go. Being honest, I think they should spend some money on renovation and clean the table a little bit.  Other food they have included hummus, Mediterranean standards and a whole fish which is amazing. I might come back for another try.
I've only eaten the lamb and rice here. I've had it a few times and every time it's the best I've ever had. The house made hot sauce is fantastic.

All week I work and I eat in Manhattan. I can write off most of my food because it’s business related, but it still hurts. So when I have my awesome dinner here at Halal Int. I feel really good. I’m having a falafel sandwich that rivals anyone’s in the city, some delicious baklava and fresh arabica coffee at a price that I’m not paying their rent. Prices are literally just a little over half what I usually have to pay for a good meal. And I feel good inside from the food. This is a awesome start to Senbet. #sankofatafari #halal #vegetarian #falafel #brooklyn #kingofcoffeenyc
